Tossed up around off, Devon Conway steps out and works it to deepish mid off for an easy single.
Comes from around the wicket to the left-hander and angles one in around the top of off middle. Devon Conway blocks it out but gets a little blow on the gloves as well.

Full and around middle, Devon Conway flicks it away with nice timing in front of mid-wicket. James Anderson from mid-wicket hares toward the ball and manages to pull it back in. Three runs are taken and New Zealand have successfully avoided the follow-on.
Hard length around off, seaming away a touch, Blundell shoulders arms.
A touch fuller and angled into the legs, Blundell tucks it 'round the corner for a single.
Pitches it up around the off stump, Conway makes a solid block off the front foot.
This is on a perfect length and angled onto middle, Conway defends it out.
Floated up, very full and on middle, Blundell blocks it out.
A tad shorter and around off, Blundell goes on the back foot and punches it out toward cover.
Full and drifting onto middle and on off, Blundell keeps it out.
Slower and shorter on off stump, pushed out onto the off side off the back foot.
Can't pierce the gap! Short again, Tom Blundell rocks back and punches it straight to cover.
Good fielding and that will be a maiden for Jack Leach. Tossed up on the pads, Blundell steps out and flicks it to the right of mid-wicket where Harry Brook makes a sharp stop.
Shorter in length around off, punched away toward cover.
Very slow through the air and shorter in length as well, Conway waits for it and makes the block.
FOUR! Fast hands from Devon Conway. Short and wide, Conway hops on the back foot and pounces on the loose ball as he cuts it hard and behind point for a boundary.
Flighted delivery on the stumps, kept out.
This is around the pads, Conway goes back in his crease and works it away in front of square leg for a couple of runs. The 50 partnership is up between these, a crucial stand this for New Zealand.
Floated up full and on off, Conway defends it out with soft hands.
Flighted delivery, drifted onto middle, Blundeel blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up around leg stump, Blundell uses his feet and flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
Shortens the length now and angles it onto the pads, Blundell pushes it out to mid on.
FOUR! Top shot! Tossed up on middle and leg, Tom Blundell uses hi feet and drives it straight back past mid on and into the fence.
Flighted delivery on the stumps, blocked out.
This is fuller and drifted onto middle, Blundell keeps it out.
Tossed up around middle, Conway drives it inside out to short cover.
Gives it a lot of air and bowls it well wide of the off stump, tempting the batter but Conway leaves it alone.
Around off, kept out.
Tosses it up full and outside off, left alone by Conway.
Pulls the length back and tries to attack the off stump, Conway gets a good stride forward and blocks it out.
Flatter one outside off, Devon Conway lets it through to the keeper. A maiden!
Shorter and on off, Blundell goes on the back foot and pushes it back to the bowler.
Drifted onto middle, Blundell makes another easy block.
Just fractionally short and around off, this is eased out toward cover.
Nagging length, around off and just turning away a touch, Blundell goes back and across to push it onto the off side.
Short again and outside off, Blundell latches onto the width and taps it toward cover for a quick single.
Floated up around off, Devon Conway gets on the front foot and presents a dead bat at it. That will be the end of the first session on Day 2 as New Zealand still trail by 187 runs.
WIDE! Banged in short and around off, Tom Blundell sways away and lets it go. The ball sails over the batter's head and it is signalled as a wide.
Goes short again but a bit down the leg side, Tom Blundell gets inside the line of the delivery and leaves it alone.
Persists with short length at the batter, Tom Blundell rises to fend this one but gets hit on the gloves. Luckily for him, the ball does not lob up.
Short of a length on leg, Tom Blundell gets on his toes and works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Slower and into the wicket outside off, Devon Conway plays a controlled pull shot to deep square leg for a single.
Keeps it short and on off, Tom Blundell gets on top of the bounce and works it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length on middle, Tom Blundell tucks this one off his hips to deep backward square leg. Retains the strike with a single.
Starts with a flighted delivery, full around off, Tom Blundell gets forward and pushes it to extra cover.
Tossed up, full at the stumps, Tom Blundell steps out and drills it back past the bowler but fails to get it past the substitute fielder Matthew Potts at mid on.
Fuller around off, Tom Blundell presses forward and defends it to cover.
FOUR! Nicely played! Fraction short and on off by Jack Leach, Tom Blundell rocks back in his crease and punches it on the off side. Pierces the gap in the covers region and collects a boundary.
Floated, full on middle, Tom Blundell pushes it back to the bowler. Jack Leach collects and fires a throw back at the striker's end.
Full on middle, Tom Blundell gets forward and keeps it out.
Short and around off, Devon Conway gets on top of the bounce and pulls it on the bounce towards square leg.
Short of a length on leg by Ben Stokes, Devon Conway swivels in the crease and pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Continues with short stuff and bowls it on leg, Tom Blundell gets inside the line of the delivery and helps it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Short again and outside off, Devon Conway tries to drag this one towards leg side but hits it a bit uppishly. Gets it between square leg and mid-wicket.
Shortish delivery at the batter, Devon Conway pulls it along the ground to fine leg and rotates the strike.
Another short delivery on leg, Tom Blundell rises and works it to fine leg for a single. 150 comes up for New Zealand.
Tossed up, full on middle and leg, Tom Blundell shimmies down the track and goes down the ground but cannot beat James Anderson at mid on.

Leach floats this one full and on off, Tom Blundell steps out but does not get to the pitch of the delivery but still goes through with the shot. Slices this one over mid off and collects a couple of runs. Ollie Robinson back tracked but it was out of his reach.
Flighted, full at the stumps, Tom Blundell presses forward and blocks it out.
Fuller on off, Tom Blundell drives this one straight to mid off.
Short and on off, Tom Blundell goes on the back foot and punches it straight to cover.
Flatter and quicker at the stumps, Tom Blundell keeps this one out.
Continues to go short and bowls it on off, Devon Conway gets on top of the bounce and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket.
Banged in short again and on off, Devon Conway goes for the pull but does not manage to execute the shot this time. Mishits it to mid-wicket.
NO BALL! Short and at the batter, Devon Conway pulls it along the ground to fine leg for a single. Ben Stokes has overstepped and it is signalled as a no ball.
Back of a length angling down the leg side, Tom Blundell gets inside the line and tucks it to the left of fine leg for a single.
Bumper outside off, Devon Conway does not reach out to the delivery and leaves it alone.
Short of a length on middle, Devon Conway rides on top of the bounce and pulls it to deep backward square leg for a single.
NO BALL! Short but angling down the leg side, Tom Blundell pulls this one towards fine leg and rotates the strike. Stokes has overstepped again.

OUT! CAUGHT! The short ball ploy does the trick for England! Ben Stokes goes short again and bowls it outside off, Devon Conway does not get on top of the bounce but still tries to drag this one on the leg side. Ends up pulling this one straight to Ollie Pope at square leg who makes no mistake. England are delighted and so they should be. New Zealand have been pegged back once again and they are now 6 wickets down.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Ben Stokes

Commentary: Full and quicker on off, Tom Blundell drives this one to mid on for a dot.
Short and around off, Tom Blundell punches it off the back foot but cannot beat Ben Duckett at extra cover.
Short and fraction outside off, Tom Blundell picks the length early and rocks back in his crease. Cuts it late and gets it past backward point for three runs.
Short and turning in on off, Michael Bracewell gets behind the line and defends it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Just wide! Flighted, fuller around off by Jack Leach, Michael Bracewell uses his feet and plays this one with the turn. Drives it uppishly but gets it just wide of the diving Ollie Robinson at mid on for a boundary.
Tossed up, full at the stumps, Michael Bracewell advances and goes for a hoick across the line. Gets it over mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Short and outside off, Tom Blundell does not reach out to the delivery and leaves it alone.

NO BALL AND FOUR! Short and punished! Goes short again and at the batter, Tom Blundell gets into the positon early and pulls it hard on the leg side. Gets it through square leg for a boundary. Ben Stokes has overstepped again, his third no ball in two overs.
Slower and into the wicket on leg, Tom Blundell gets into the shot early as he tried to pull. Gets a top edge but it falls in no man's land behind square on the leg side for a single.
Slower and a touch fuller but down the leg side, Michael Bracewell leaves the ball alone.
Banged in short on off, Michael Bracewell ducks under it and lets it go.
Sharp bouncer! Ben Stokes goes short again and bowls it at the batter, Michael Bracewell rises to defend but gets rapped on the gloves. The ball drops safely on the off side.
Short and on leg, Michael Bracewell ducks underneath the delivery and lets it go.
Tossed up, full on middle, Tom Blundell presses forward and defends.
Tossed up, full on middle, Tom Blundell uses his feet and works it to mid on.
FOUR! Flighted, full around off, Tom Blundell shimmies down the track and slices this one over Ben Stokes at mid off for a boundary.
Short and flatter on off, Tom Blundell cuts this one to deep point for a single.
Short and turning into the batter, Michael Bracewell smothers the ball on the leg side.
Short and on leg, Michael Bracewell stays back and works it to short leg.
Starts with a short delivery aimed at the batter, Tom Blundell gets inside the line and leaves it alone.
Short and on middle and leg, Tom Blundell gets on top of the bounce and pulls it towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Shorter and on off, Michael Bracewell hangs back and drops this one on the off side. Tom Blundell calls him for a quick single and he obliges.
Persists with short length but down the leg side, Tom Blundell leaves the ball alone.
Switches to 'round the wicket, bowls it short and on leg, Tom Blundell works this one off his hips to deep backward square leg for a single.

Leg bye! Ouch, that is a tough blow! Banged into the wicket at the batter by Ben Stokes, Michael Bracewell ducks to evade the delivery but the ball does not bounce and hits him flush on the helmet. The ball rolls towards off side and batters cross for a single.
Slower and short, turning into the batter, Michael Bracewell stays back and keeps it out.
Short and on off, Michael Bracewell pushes this one off the back foot to cover.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another soft dismissal and this time it is Michael Bracewell! Jack Leach floats this one full at the stumps, Michael Bracewell gets tempted by the flight and steps out to go down the ground, Does not get the elevation and he hits it straight to Ben Stokes at mid on. Jack Leach has his first wicket of the game and New Zealand are now 7 down with still 143 runs behind.
Howout: c Ben Stokes b Jack Leach

Commentary: Full and flatter on off, Scott Kuggeleijn keeps this one out.
Flighted, full on middle, Scott Kuggeleijn presses forward and defends it on the leg side.
Short and quicker just outside off, Scott Kuggeleijn stays on the back foot and punches it straight to cover.
Starts with a shortish delivery at the batter, Tom Blundell swivels and pulls only to find square leg.
Short of a length on leg, Tom Blundell pulls it along the ground to backward square leg. A slight fumble there by Joe Root allows the batters to cross for a single.
Short and on leg by Stuart Broad, Scott Kuggeleijn is late on the pull and gets it off his gloves towards fine leg for a single. Also, Scott Kuggeleijn is off the mark in Test cricket.
Short again and on middle, Tom Blundell rides on top of the bounce and pulls it along the ground but fails to get it past square leg.
Back of a length down the leg side, Tom Blundell looks to tuck this one fine on the leg side but misses.
Another bumper at the batter by Stuart Broad, Tom Blundell gets inside the line to pull this one but fails to connect.
Flighted, full around off, Scott Kuggeleijn gets on the front foot and defends.
Full and angling in on middle, Scott Kuggeleijn blocks it out.

SIX! Scott Kuggeleijn goes huge! Jack Leach floats this one full on middle, Scott Kuggeleijn gets down on one knee and executes the slog sweep to perfection. Clears the mid-wicket fence with ease and collects a maximum.
FOUR! Another delivery tossed up, full around off, Scott Kuggeleijn steps out and drills it back past the bowler. Beats the mid off fielder as well and collects a boundary.
Goes short and on off, Scott Kuggeleijn stays on the back foot and defends it on the off side.
Short and at the stumps, Scott Kuggeleijn works this one on the leg side for a dot.
This is dragged down the leg side, Tom Blundell just pulls it down to fine leg and gets across for a single. And, that will be FIFTY for Blundell, it has been a fighting knock from him.
Goes full and bowls it on off stump, Scott Kuggeleijn is late on the block and the ball almost sneaks through but luckily for him, it takes the inside edge and goes past the stumps.
Banged in short and over middle, Scott Kuggeleijn pulls it well and in front of square on the leg side for a couple of runs.
Comes from around the wicket now and digs it in halfway down the track over leg stump. Scott Kuggeleijn ducks under it well.
FOUR! Hammered away! Fractionally short and around off, Kuggeleijn stays on the back foot and pulls it hard and through wide mid on for a boundary. The 200 is now up for New Zealand.
And again but this it is hit straight to the man. Banged in short and around off, Kuggeleijn pulls it toward mid-wicket.
Nagging length, angled into the leg stump, Blundell goes on the back foot and keeps it out.
Floated up around off, Blundell backs away a bit and pushes it onto the off side.
Tosses it up now on off stump, Tom Blundell uses his feet well but drills it straight to mid on.
Flatter and around middle, nudged away onto the leg side.

Poor cricket all around! Around off stump, Tom Blundell pushes it out in front of cover and looks for a single but he is sent back. Ben Duckett there picks up the ball and fires in a low throw wide of the keeper and there's no one backing up. The ball rolls away into the fence and that will be the easiest four Blundell has scored in this game.

FOUR! Up and over! Flighted delivery on middle, Tom Blundell dances down the track and forces the lofted shot well over mid on for a boundary. New Zealand now eating away into the English quickly here.
This is banged in short and over off, this is pulled down to mid-wicket.
Shorter and on the body, Kuggeleijn gets inside the line and jabs it toward short fine leg for a quick run.
Banged in short and over middle, Tom Blundell mistimes the pull shot through wide mid on and picks up a couple of runs.
Fractionally short and over the stumps, Tom Blundell hangs back and rolls his wrists over the ball before pulling it down to deep backward square leg for a brace. New Zealand now trail by 111!
A yorker now around middle and leg, Tom Blundell stays deep in his crease and jams it out toward short fine leg for a quick single.
Short and on the body, pulled straight to backward square leg.
Starts with a good-length delivery around off, a hint of inward movement, Tom Blundell takes a stride forward to defend but gets an inside edge back onto his pads.
On a length on off, Tom Blundell hangs back and defends this one to mid-wicket.
Back of a length at the stumps, Tom Blundell works this from the crease towards mid-wicket.
Excellent running! Good length around off and swinging back in, Tom Blundell blocks it off the front foot and sets off for the run straightaway.
A touch fuller and angling it into the stumps, Kuggeleijn keeps it out.
Fuller and outside off, Kuggeleijn reaches out and pushes it toward cover.
FOUR! Skillful from Tom Blundell! Just a fraction short and outside off, Blundell stays back and knocks the ball down as it goes past him through the gully region and into the fence.
Fullish length on off, kept out.
Broad angles this one into the pads, Blundell gets on the front foot and flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
On a length and angled into middle and leg, Blundell works it away through square leg for one.
This is pitched up on the fifth stump line, Kuggeleijn leaves it alone.
Fuller and attacking the off stump, kept out.
Half an appeal for caught behind but the umpire isn't interested. Fuller in length and angling down leg, Tom Blundell looks to flick but misses and the ball flicks the pad on its way to the keeper.

A huge appeal this time for lbw but it is turned down yet again! James Anderson bowls it on a length around middle and angles it into the pads. Tom Blundell gets caught on the crease and the ball goes past the inside edge and Blundell is rapped on the pads. This time Ben Stokes does review it. Nothing on UltraEdge and Ball Tracking shows that the ball is missing leg stump.

FOUR! Good length around off, Tom Blundell dabs it down with soft hands and runs it down to third man for a boundary. New Zealand now trail by exactly a 100 runs and these are frustrating runs now for England.
Goes full and straight now, Blundell punches it straight back to the bowler.
Length ball on off, blocked out.
Good length around the top of off, Blundell blocks it off the front foot.
Back of a length around off, Kuggeleijn pushes it off the back foot to the left of mid off for a quick single.
On a hard length around off, Tom Blundell dabs it down in front of cover-point.
A tad shorter and around off, Blundell hops back and nudges it down toward backward point for one.
Goes full now and bowls it on off stump, Kuggeleijn keeps it out.
A length ball around off, Kuggeleijn defends it out.
Good length on off stump, blocked out by Kuggeleijn.

EDGED AND GONE! Or is it? Tom Blundell has reviewed it straight away! James Anderson bowls this on a good length around off and the ball nips back in sharply off the deck. Blundell gets cut in half as the ball beats the bat but might have taken an inside edge. UltraEDge though shows that it is missing the bat and hitting the pads rather. Ball Tracking is checked for lbw as well but the ball is missing the wickets and it is an excellent review by Blundell. Not Out!
Good length around middle, Blundell flicks it away in front of mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Full and around off, pushed away onto the off side.
Bowls it a bit fuller and on middle, Blundell flicks it uppishly toward mid-wicket.
Back of a length outside off, Blundell stays on the back foot and guides it through backward point for one.
Full and straight, blocked out by Kuggeleijn.
Inside-edge! Good length angling into middle and leg, Tom Blundell looks to tuck it away but gets a big inside edge back onto the pads.
Pitches this one up around off stump, Blundell drives it to the right of mid off and picks up a couple of runs. The 50-run stand is up between these two as well.
Length ball onto the pads, tucked away 'round the corner for a single.
Goes wider of the crease and angles it into the stumps, Kuggeleijn works it away to square leg.
Nagging length, in that channel around off, Kuggeleijn goes on the back foot to keep it out.
Swish and a miss! This is dug in short and outside off, Scott Kuggeleijn looks to rock ball and pull but is well beaten.
Length ball around off, Tom Blundell puts a stride across and bunts it out.
Good length, angling into the pads, Blundell looks to work it leg side but misses. The ball rolls off the pads onto the off side and they get a leg bye.
Good length around off, blocked out by Kuggeleijn.
Pitched up on off stump, tucked away to short mid-wicket.
Full and angled into middle, nudged away leg side.
A bit shorter and outside off, Kuggeleijn steers it down through backward point for a single.
Good length on the fifth stump line, left alone by Kuggeleijn.

OUT! TIMBER! A peach of a delivery from Ollie Robinson and the resistance from Scott Kuggeleijn comes to an end! Robinson bowls this fuller on off and angles it in but not quite full to drive. Kuggeleijn is drawn forward and he looks to play the on drive. In the end, Kuggeleijn ends up playing all around a straight ball and the ball goes crashing into the stumps as well. New Zealand are 8 down now. Also, Tim Southee walks out to bat now.
Howout: b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Shorter in length and over off, Tim Southee hops and keeps it down.
Full and wide, Southee caresses it through extra cover for a couple of runs.
This is dug in short and over the stumps, Tim Southee ducks under it well.
This is pitched up on off stump, Tim Southee pushes it straight back toward the left of mid on for a single. That will be the end of the second session on Day 2!
Starts off with a flighted delivery, full and on middle, Tim Southee eases it onto the off side.
Tossed up around off, Southee blocks it toward cover.
Drifted onto leg stump, Tim Southee advances and pushes it toward deepish mid off for an easy single.
Drifted onto the pads, Tom Blundell nudges it 'round the corner and gets across to the other end.
Nicely tossed up on middle, Southee backs away and hits it straight to the bowler.
Flatter one, a tad bit short and close to the off pole. Tim Southee cuts it off the outer half of the bat toward short third man for a single.
Back of a length around off, Tim Southee with a back-foot punch to get the ball through covers for a run.
Pitches it a bit further up and angles it into middle and leg, Tom Blundell looks to block off the front foot but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On a hard length outside off, Blundell stays back and dabs it down through backward point for one more.
FOUR! Glorious from the skipper! Overpitched and on middle, Tim Southee stays leg side of the ball and hammers it right back past the bowler for a lovely boundary.
Here comes the bumper now, around the off stump and angling in, Southee ducks under it.

OUT! TAKEN! Tim Southee cannot believe his luck! A low full toss from Ollie Robinson at the stumps, Southee walks across and gets inside the line of the ball before lapping it hard and flat over backward square leg. Unluckily for Southee, Ben Duckett stationed over there is well inside the ropes and does well to pick the ball out of the sun rays as he leaps up and pouches it safely. England are now one wicket away from bundling New Zealand out and they still lead by 78 runs.
Howout: c Ben Duckett b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Shorter and on off, Tom Blundell goes on the back foot to keep it out.
Slower through the air and fuller around off, Tom Blundell looks for the paddle sweep but fails to get it away.

SIX! Well then, Tom Blundell has decided to take matters into his own hands. Drifted onto the leg stump, Blundell steps down the track and clubs it over the wide long on fence for a maximum. The 250 is now up for New Zealand.
Nagging length outside off, Tom Blundell hangs back and dabs it late toward short third man.

FOUR! Excellent shot again from Tom Blundell and he moves into the 90s! Flighted delivery, drifting into middle and leg, Blundell shimmies down the track and lofts it inside out one-bounce over the cover fence.

FOUR! Just over! This is dragged down by Jack Leach around off, a real 'hit-me' delivery. Tom Blundell rocks back and has to wait for it before he pulls it hard and flat just over the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary.
Pitched up on off stump, Blair Tickner with a solid front-foot defense and the crowd cheers it as well.
Good length, angling into middle, Tickner blocks it out.
Good length in that channel around off and just holding its line. Tickner watches it all the way through and leaves it alone.
Goes full now and looks to target the toes but just slides it down the leg side.
Good length around the top of off, Tickner with another solid block off the front foot. Can he now survive one more delivery and allow Tom Blundell to have a shot at his century?

As close as it gets and the crowd is fixed in on this game. Ollie Robinson goes full and straight and gets it in the blockhole. Blair Tickner with a nervy defense but somehow he manages to get a bit of bat on it and keeps it out.

In the air but safe and Tom Blundell inches closer and closer to his ton. Jack Leach shortens the length and bowls it around off stump. Blundell skips down the track and looks for the big hoick across the line but is a bit undone in flight. The ball takes the top edge and loops up over the slip fielder and they get back for two.
Short and flatter at the stumps, Tom Blundell goes back in his crease and pushes it back to the bowler.

HUNDRED for Tom Blundell! What an innings this has been the wicketkeeper batter! Jack Leach bowls this one slower and short at the stumps, Tom Blundell gets into the position early and paddles this one towards the vacant fine leg region. Gets enough bat on it to come back for the second to bring up a well-deserved hundred.
Short and on middle, Tom Blundell goes on the back foot and works it on the leg side for a dot.
Short and quicker on off, Tom Blundell makes room to cut this one but fails to connect.
Tossed up, full on off, Tom Blundell gets down and goes for the slog sweep. Does not get it from the middle part of the bat but gets it in the gap and crosses for a single.
On a length at the stumps, Tom Blundell steps out and frees his arms to go through the off side but gets an under edge that rolls behind the wicket.
Fuller and angling in around off, Tom Blundell takes a stride forward and leaves it alone.
Length delivery on middle, Tom Blundell hangs back and works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Smart batting by Tom Blundell! Ollie Robinson bowls a fullish delivery on off, Tom Blundell gets across and scoops this one towards the fine leg region for a boundary.
FOUR! Cracking shot by Tom Blundell! Back of a length on middle by Ollie Robinson, Tom Blundell backs away and frees his arms. Slaps this one back over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Full and drifting at the pads, Tom Blundell misses the clip and gets hit on the front pad. It will be Blair Tickner on strike for the next over.

Short and on off, Blair Tickner dabs this one towards cover-point and sets off for a single. But gets sent back by Tom Blundell. The fielder fires a throw at the striker's end which Ben Foakes fails to collect. Blair Tickner gets back in the nick of the time.
Keeps it short and on off, Blair Tickner keeps this one out.
Tossed up, full around off, Blair Tickner presses forward and blocks it out on the off side.
Short and angling in on leg, Blair Tickner stays back and defends it on the leg side.
Flighted, full on middle, Blair Tickner gets forward and blocks this one out.
Short and flatter at the stumps, Blair Tickner gets behind the line of the ball and defends it down the wicket.
Touch slower and on a length on off, Tom Blundell hangs back and defends it on the off side.
On a length on middle, Tom Blundell works this one towards deep mid-wicket and decides not to take the single.
Slower delivery again, on a length around off, Tom Blundell gets behind the line and blocks this one out.
Fuller and on off by Ollie Robinson, Tom Blundell takes a stride forward and keeps this one out.
Looks to go for the yorker but bowls a full toss at the batter, Tom Blundell advances but gets cramped for room and can only push it to mid on.

FOUR! Streaky but they all count! Slower and fuller outside off, Tom Blundell clears his front leg to thump this one down the ground but gets into his shot early. Gets an outside edge that goes over Joe Root at first slip and the ball trickles to the boundary.
Back of a length at the stumps by Ben Stokes, Blair Tickner sways away and leaves the ball alone.
Another back-of-a-length delivery at the batter, Blair Tickner stays leg side of the ball and lets it go.
Short and aimed at the batter, Blair Tickner fends this one awkwardly towards gully.
Short of a length on leg, Blair Tickner takes his one hand off the bat and fends it off his gloves towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! Short again and on middle, Tom Blundell does not miss out as he swivels in his crease and pulls it hard towards deep square leg for a boundary. These are important runs for New Zealand.

Slower and full outside off, Tom Blundell gets down and swings hard at the delivery. Gets a thickish outside edge that flies to the right of the keeper. Ben Foakes flings himself to his right but fails to hang onto it. The batters cross for a single.
Fullish and on off by Ollie Robinson, Tom Blundell gets across and scoops this one wide of fine leg. Jack Leach there makes a good diving stop and saves a couple of runs for his side.
Short and on off, Tom Blundell pulls this one hard but fails to get it past Stuart Broad at mid-wicket.
Shortish delivery again and on middle, Tom Blundell pulls this one to deep square leg and refuses the single.
Slower and into the wicket outside off, Tom Blundell looks to drag this one on the leg side but does not connect.
Short and at the batter, Tom Blundell pulls this one towards Ben Duckett at deep backward square leg and takes the singe this time.
Short of a length on middle and leg, Blair Tickner gets behind the line and solidly keeps this one out.
Slower and tad short on leg, Tom Blundell waits for it and pulls it towards fine leg. No single taken.
Cutter on a length on middle, Tom Blundell clears his front leg and goes for a mighty heave across the line. Gets it from the inner part of the bat towards deep square leg and denies the single.
FOUR! Slower and short at the batter, Tom Blundell does not miss out this time as he pulls this one to the right of deep square leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Pace on this time by Ben Stokes and bowls it on middle, Tom Blundell gets on his toes and flat bats this one through the vacant mid on region for yet another boundary.
Short and angling down the leg side, Tom Blundell helps this one towards fine leg and takes the single.
On a good length around off, Blair Tickner shuffles a bit and keeps this one out.
Starts with a length delivery swinging away outside off, Tom Blundell shimmies down the track and tries to go down the ground but connects with thin air.

Full and a hint of away movement on middle, Tom Blundell tries to turn this one on the leg side but ends up chipping this one towards mid on. Luckily for him, the ball falls short of the diving Stuart Broad at mid on.
Goes full and on off, Tom Blundell takes a stride forward and defends it on the off side.
Back of a length at the batter by James Anderson, Tom Blundell works this one off the back foot to mid-wicket.
Back of a length at the batter by James Anderson, Tom Blundell works this one off the back foot to mid-wicket.

FOUR! James Anderson goes back of a length and swinging away outside off, Tom Blundell steps out and frees his arms. Slogs across the line but gets a top edge that goes over the third man fielder for a boundary.
Full and swinging in outside off, Blair Tickner shoulders arms and lets it go.
On a good length and angling into the batter, Blair Tickner keeps this one out off the back foot.
Fuller in length and a bit too wide outside off, Blair Tickner leaves the ball alone.
Full and swinging in on middle and leg, Blair Tickner accounts for the swing and clips it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.

Full and outside off by Stuart Broad, Blair Tickner pushes at the delivery away from his body but gets beaten on the outside edge. Ben Foakes goes up in appeal thinking Tickner has edged it. The umpire shakes his head and Ben Stokes isn't convinced enough to go upstairs. Would you believe it? The UltraEdge show a spike as the ball was next to he bat. A huge reprieve for Blair Tickner.
Full and at the stumps, Blair Tickner gets behind the line and keeps this one out.
On a length on middle, Tom Blundell defends this one on the leg side.
Fuller in length around off, Tom Blundell takes a stride forward and blocks this one out on the off side.
FOUR! More frustration for England! Bowls this one on a length and drifting at the pads, Tom Blundell helps this one fine towards the fine leg region for a boundary.
On a good length outside off, Tom Blundell shoulders arms and leaves the ball alone.

OUT! CAUGHT! New Zealand have been bowled out for 306! Back of a length on middle by James Anderson, Tom Blundell shimmies down the track and looks to slap this one down the ground. Skies this one high in the air and only as far as James Anderson who settles under it and does the rest. End of a brilliant knock by Tom Blundell but it is England with a slender lead of 19 runs.
Howout: c & b James Anderson

Commentary: Starts with a back-of-a-length delivery in the channel outside off, a hint of away movement, Zak Crawley shoulders arms and leaves the ball alone.
Strays at the pads on a length, Zak Crawley tucks this one to square leg and opens his account with a single.
Length delivery swinging into the batter on middle, Ben Duckett gets behind the line and defends it down the wicket.
Goes full this time and shaping in on middle, Ben Duckett gets across and works it to mid-wicket.
Full and going across outside off, Ben Duckett drives this one a bit uppishly but wide of mid off. Scott Kuggeleijn performs the chase and puts in a dive to save a run for his side.
Beauty! On a length and just outside off, the ball straightens after pitching, Zak Crawley looks to defend this one but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full and swinging away on off by Neil Wagner, Ben Duckett gets behind the line and defends it back to the bowler.
On a length and outside off, Ben Duckett pushes this one towards cover but fails to find the gap.
Length delivery on off, Ben Duckett stays back and defends it on the leg side.
Full and going away on off, Ben Duckett gets forward and solidly blocks this one out.
Goes full again and allows the ball to swing away on off, Ben Duckett drives it with a straight bat to mid on.
FOUR! Keeps it full and just outside off, Ben Duckett gets the width he needs and pounces on it. Drives this one to the left of mid off and collects a boundary.
On a good length and swinging away outside off, a loose shot by Zak Crawley as he drives away from the body. He is lucky to not get an edge there.
Length delivery angling at the pads, Zak Crawley turns this one to mid-wicket.
Full and around off by Tim Southee, Zak Crawley takes a stride forward and defends it to cover.
Goes full again and in the channel outside off, Zak Crawley solidly blocks this one out down the wicket.
Full and outside off, Zak Crawley goes for the drive without much foot movement and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full and slanting at the pads, Zak Crawley clips this one along the ground to deep square leg and retains the strike with a single.
FOUR! Full and going across outside off, Zak Crawley frees his arms and slices this one past backward point for his first boundary.
Fuller and outside off from over the wicket,, Zak Crawley shoulders arms and leaves the ball alone.
On a length and outside off, Zak Crawley shapes to cut this one but shoulders his arms at the last moment.

FOUR! Short and punished by Zak Crawley! Neil Wagner goes a bit short this time and outside off, it sits up nicely for the batter. Zak Crawley stays on the back foot and cuts it through covers for a boundary.
FOUR MORE! Short again and outside off, Zak Crawley frees his arms and cuts it late this time. Gets it past backward point for yet another boundary.
Full and angling away on off, Zak Crawley takes a stride forward and defends it on the off side.
Full and outside off, Ben Duckett drives it off the front foot to mid off.
FOUR! Cut away by Ben Duckett! A fraction short and outside off, Ben Duckett uses the angle to his advantage and cuts it past backward point for a boundary.
Switches to 'round the wicket and goes full around off, Ben Duckett gets forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length on off by Tim Southee, Ben Duckett hangs back and defends. The ball drops at his feet and he keeps it out from rolling onto the stumps. .
Length delivery on middle, Ben Duckett gets behind and pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length on off, Ben Duckett punches this one off the back foot but fails to beat Michael Bracewell at cover-point.
Starts off with a good-length delivery over off stump, Zak Crawley goes on the back foot and eases it toward cover.
Back of a length around off, this is kept down on the off side.
Bangs it in a bit and bowls it just outside off, Zak Crawley looks to hop and cut it over point but is beaten by the extra bounce.

FOUR! New Zealand continue to just keep on conceding boundaries. This is short and over off, Zak Crawley gets in a great position and muscles it well in front of square on the leg side for a boundary.
Good length around the top of off, tentatively kept out by Crawley.
Goes full now and bowls it around off, Crawley drives it straight to cover.
FOUR! That's impressive from Ben Duckett. A good-length ball, angling in a long way from well outside off. Duckett stays back and plays it very late as he just taps it behind point for a boundary.
Full and around off, driven firmly to short cover.

A bit of a loose shot from Duckett this time around. Tim Southee pushes this one well outside the off stump and keeps the length full. Duckett looks for the expansive drive away from the body but is beaten.

EDGED AND FOUR! Nagging length, brings the ball close to the off stump and draws the batter forward. Ben Duckett leans forward to drive but gets a thick outside edge that flies wide of the man at second slip and rolls into the fence.
Nicely bowled! Immaculate length, close to the off stump and straightening a touch as well. Duckett has a little nibble at it but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Full and wide again, Duckett throws his hands at it and slashes it toward deep point for a single.
Good length around the pads, Duckett tucks it away in front of square leg for an easy single.
On a good length just over off stump, Zak Crawley gets pushed onto the back foot and ends up edging it down to the slip cordon with soft hands.
Just a fraction fuller and on off stump, Crawley blocks it out.
Goes full and straight now, Crawley drives it straight to short mid on.
FOUR! Hit on the up! Pitched up around off, Zak Crawley punches it in between extra cover and mid off and finds the fence. Excellent timing on that.

FOUR! This time on the other side of the wicket. Back of a length around middle, Zak Crawley short-arm jabs it well in front of square on the on-side and picks up back-to-back boundaries. England are off to a flier once again.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Ben Duckett cuts it toward deep point for a single.

Risky single! A length ball around off, Zak Crawley hits it firmly to the right of cover where Kane Williamson makes a half-stop and they go for the run. Neil Wagner then picks up the ball and has a shy at the bowler's end. He misses and the replays show that Crawley was well home anyway.
Good length, on a tight line around off stump. Ben Duckett just has a feel for it and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Another quick run and the 50 is up for England! Back of a length around off, tapped away straight to point for one.
Bowls it fuller and outside off, Crawley looks to drive but gets a leading edge onto the off side.
Pitches it up outside off, and Zak Crawley just lets it through to the keeper.

Full and wide outside off, Ben Duckett extends his arms and slashes it away behind backward point. Kane Williamson from deep point runs around and fumbles a bit, allowing the batters to get back for the second.

OUT! CAUGHT! New Zealand have their first wicket and Blair Tickner is absolutely elated! Tickner bowls it on a good length, angling it across the left-hander and keeps the line tight on off stump. Ben Duckett stays rooted to his crease and pushes at it with hard hands only to get an outside edge on it. The ball goes straight into the bread basket of Tom Latham at second slip and he holds on with both hands while tumbling over. Tickner gets the better of Duckett for the second time in this game.
Howout: c Tom Latham b Blair Tickner

Commentary: Full and outside off, Ollie Pope stays watchful and leaves it alone.
Good length at the stumps, Ollie Pope decides to walk down the track but ends up just blocking it back to the bowler.
Good length around the off stump, kept out by Pope.
Just a fraction shorter and on leg stump, Ollie Pope comes forward and works it 'round the corner for a single.
This is pitched up on the fifth stump line and swinging away. Ollie Pope leaves it alone.
Southee keeps the ball full but brings it closer to the off stump, swinging it away. Pope makes another leave and the ball just keeps really low.

Play and a miss! Perfect length from Tim Southee and bowls it outside off, Ollie Pope looks to cream the cover drive but is beaten past the outside edge as the ball seams away beautifully off the deck.

FOUR! Much better from Ollie Pope and that's a brilliant shot. Fullish length outside off,m trying to swing it away, Pope advances and drives it square of the wicket through cover-point for a boundary.

Just keeping the batter honest here. Ollie Pope is already looking to get outside the crease and Tim Southee just bowls a scrambled-seam delivery on a good length around off. Pope shoulders arms but the ball nips back in late and goes past the off stump.
Length ball on off stump, Ollie Pope blocks it out. A good over of Test cricket comes to an end with the batter and bowler both trading blows.
On a good length around off, Zak Crawley pats it away onto the off side.
Sliding down leg! Bowls it a touch fuller and around middle, angling it in. Zak Crawley falls over a bit as he looks to flick and gets hit on the pads.
Good length on the pads, this is worked away behind square leg for a single. Also, Blair Tickner has overstepped and a no ball is called.
FOUR! Nice use of the feet by Ollie Pope. Length again on middle and leg, Pope comes forward and just pushes it wide of mid on to pick up a boundary.
Fuller in length and around off, kept out by Pope.
FOUR! Exquisite timing from Ollie Pope! Overpitched and outside off, Pope gets on the front foot and drives it through the big gap at cover for yet another boundary.
On a hard length and around off, Pope taps it onto the off side.
Good length around the top of off, Zak Crawley blocks it out.
Lovely outswinger by Tim Southee. This is pitched up around the fourth stump line and drawing the batter forward. Crawley looks to play at it but is undone completely by the swing.
Fullish length around off, pushed away to cover.

Just a bit too high probably! Tim Southee bowls this on a length and around the pads, looking for the magic ball. Southee does get it to swing away and Zak Crawley gets wrapped high on the pads as he looks to flick. There is a loud appeal for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Full and around off, swinging away, a bit too full though to draw the batter forward.
Maiden! This is around off and Crawley defends it out.
Starts from a bit wider of the crease and bowls it on a good length around off. Ollie Pope watchfully blocks it out.
Kuggeleijn sees Ollie Pope coming forward early and bangs it in short over the stumps. Pope is able to duck under it.
Fuller and around middle, Pope steps out and works it leg side for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A bit of a nothing shot and Zak Crawley has thrown away a good start here. Scott Kuggeleijn just bangs this one on a hard length over the off stump and the ball keeps a shade low. Crawley stays on the back foot and there's no foot movement at all. Crawley plays a lazy pull shot and gets a faint toe-end of the bat. Tom Blundell takes an easy catch behind the sticks and Kuggeleijn strikes in his first over. England now lead by 87 runs.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Scott Kuggeleijn

Commentary: Banged in short and around leg stump, Stuart Broad looks to come forward and take it on but has to adjust and takes a blow on the body.

Oh my, that is a huge blunder from the Kiwis! Scott Kuggeleijn bangs it in short and over the stumps, Stuart Broad advances and takes on the pull shot. Broad only manages to sky it around the silly point region and the bowler and keeper both run toward it. In the end, both Kuggeleijn and Tom Blundell stop in their tracks and are left watching each other as the ball lands in the middle. A huge reprieve for Broad and he also gets a single.

FOUR BYES! Tim Southee comes from around the wicket and tries to angle in a full one at the toes but spills it well down the leg side. Tom Blundell puts in a big dive to his right but fails to get to it and the ball rolls away into the fence.

Right on the money! Tim Southee goes for the bumper now and gets it spot on as he bowls it over middle and off and the ball just climbs up at an awkward height. Stuart Broad hops and tries to fend it away butn instead he takes a blow on the helmet. Hope he is fine.
Another short ball, aimed at the body, Broad hops and is able to keep it down on the off side.
FOUR! Slapped away! Good length outside off, Stuart Broad sees the width and goes after it. Broad thumps it over the vacant cover region for a boundary.
Shorter and around leg stump, Broad works it off his hips past square leg for a single.

Dangerous leave from Ollie Pope but he does manage to get far enough outside the crease to avoid being given out. This is on a good length around off and just angling in. Ollie Pope comes forward and then shoulders arms expecting an outswinger but the ball flicks the pad and there is an appeal from the hosts. It is quickly turned down though.
Banged in short and at the batter from 'round the wicket, Stuart Broad ducks under it in time and lets it go through to the keeper.
Back of a length but angling down the leg side, Stuart Broad tries to help it fine behind the wicket but misses.
Sharp bumper! Scott Kuggeleijn follows the batter and bowls it short at him, Stuart Broad gets into an awkward position and fends this one towards backward square leg. No single taken.
Back of a length on middle by Scott Kuggeleijn, Stuart Broad gets on his toes to defend this one but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Keeps it back of a length around off, Stuart Broad stays leg side of the ball and dabs this one past gully. The ball rolls to third man but Broad refuses a single.

Leg bye! Short of a length on leg by Scott Kuggeleijn, Stuart Broad looks to tuck this one on the leg side but fails to get any bat on it. The ball comes off his body and rolls to fine leg for a single. That will be Stumps on Day 2!
Starts off with a no ball! Neil Wagner steams in and serves it shorter over off stump. Stuart Broad hopes and keeps it down on the off side and the umpire signals a no ball as Wagner has overstepped.
Short again and aimed at the body, Broad gets on the back foot and keeps it down on the on-side.
Wagner bangs this one in around off stump, Broad gets pushed onto the back foot and edges it down to third man for a single. England now lead by 100 runs!
A bumper now, spilled down the leg side and Ollie Pope ducks under it with ease.
This is short around leg stump and coming in at an awkward height. Pope looks to pull it behind square but mistimes it to the right of the man at backward square leg.
Good bouncer this, over middle and leg and zipping through. Ollie Pope ducks under it well.
Keeps the length short and bowls it around the hips, pulled down to fine leg for a run.
This is full and wide of the off stump, just a hint of away movement there. Pope leaves it alone.
Pitches it up now and brings the ball much closer to the off pole, Pope makes a solid block off the front foot.
Keeps the length a bit fuller and angles it into middle, Pope defends it out.
On a length and outside off, Ollie Pope shoulders arms at it.
Full and outside off, shaping away, Ollie Pope shimmies down the pitch looking to cover drive but mistimes it completely toward mid off.
Tim Southee starts the day with a maiden! Good length on the fifth stump line, Pope comes forward but ends up just leaving the delivery.

OUT! CAUGHT! That's what Neil Wagner does best! Wagner comes from over the wicket and bangs in a nasty bouncer over middle and leg. The ball shoots off the deck and comes in at an awkward height and Stuart Broad gets all cramped up. Broad hops back and turns his head away as he tries to fend it away. The ball takes the handle of the bat and lobs up around the gully region where Henry Nicholls takes a simple catch. The 'Nighthawk' is gone and New Zealand have an early breakthrough on Day 3.
Howout: c Henry Nicholls b Neil Wagner

Commentary: A bit of a loosener as Wagner bowls this short and well down the leg side. Joe Root leaves it alone.

Now a loose shot from Joe Root. Shortish length, down the leg side yet again, Root looks to pull it fine but the ball just sneaks under the bat. There is half an appeal for caught behind but nothing doing.
Short and on leg stump, pulled away toward square leg.
Oh, Joe Root has completely mistimed that! Banged in short and around leg stump, cramping Root for room as he tries to pull and almost miscues it straight toward square leg.
Shorter and on the body, pulled down toward fine leg for a single.
FOUR LEG BYES! This is fuller and on the pads, looking to swing it away but this one slides right on. Joe Root looks to flick but the ball just tickles the pads and runs away into the fine leg fence.
FOUR! Close but not close enough! Good length around the top of off, Joe Root pushes at it and gets an inside edge that goes past the stumps and runs away into the fine leg fence. A lucky boundary!
Good length again around off, Root blocks it out.
Bowls it a touch fuller and on off, Root looks to defend off the front foot but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Pitches up outside off and swinging away, Root leaves it alone.
Beaten! Tim Southee bowls this a bit wider of the off stump and brings the ball back into the right-hander. Joe Root looks to drive away from the body but is beaten on the inside edge.
SIX! Aggressive shot from Ollie Pope! Banged in around the leg stump, Pope gets inside the line of the ball and muscles it away over the fine leg fence for a maximum.
This is banged in even shorter and outside off, Ollie Pope backs away and upper cuts it wide of the man at third man for a single.
Around the hips, this is pulled down to fine leg for one more.
SIX! WOW! Short ball over middle and leg and angling across. Ollie Pope shuffles across and gets inside the line once again before pulling it onto the grass banks over the fine leg fence.
Uppish but in the gap! Banged in over leg stump, Pope takes it on and pulls it a bit uppishly in front of the diving man at mid-wicket for a single.
Keeps it short and around leg, Root pulls it down behind square leg for a run.
On a length on the fifth stump line and shaping away, Root leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
And again! Bowled wide of the off stump and swinging it away from the right-hander, Root shoulders arms.
Southee keeps the length a bit full and swings it away from the fourth stump line, Joe Root makes yet another leave.
FOUR! Pitched up around off stump, Joe Root shimmies across the wicket and works it sweetly through wide mid on and the ball runs away into the fence.
Shorter and outside off, Root plays it late and dabs it down wide of the gully fielder who gets a hand on it. They pick up a single.
Good length outside off and shooting of the deck a bit. Ollie Pope advances but leaves it alone.
Shorter in length and over middle and leg, Joe Root pulls it along the ground past square leg for a run.
Back of a length and outside off, tapped away off the back foot and to deep point for an easy single.

SIX! A third maximum in the same region and this time it's off the bat of Joe Root. Neil Wagner bangs in a bumper across middle and Root is able to get across the stumps and pull it over the man at fine leg for a biggie.
Slower one, around the hips, this is nudged down to fine leg for one.

SIX! All the way again and England are quickly extending their lead here. Wagner comes from 'round the wicket and bangs it in shorter just over head height as well. Ollie Pope still takes it on and pulls it over the fine leg fence yet again for a maximum.
Back to over the wicket now and dug in over leg stump, Pope pulls it to deep mid-wicket for one.
On a good length outside off and shaping away a touch, left alone for the keeper to collect.
Fuller and at the stumps, Pope advances and whips it away through mid-wicket for a single.
Good length around off and just angling in a bit, Root gets on the front foot and blocks it out.
Full and around off, shaping away, Root drives it straight to the man at short extra cover.
Pitched up around off, Joe Root punches it to the right of the diving man at short extra cover for a quick single.
This is full and outside off, Pope leaves it alone.
Scott Kuggeleijn comes back into the attack and starts off with a back-of-a-length delivery on the body. This is tucked away 'round the corner for one and the lead is now worth 150 runs.
Top delivery! On a hard length, angled in from wider of the crease and into off stump. Ollie Pope looks to block but the ball straightens and zips past the outside edge.
On middle, Pope comes forward and flicks it leg side for a single. The 50-run stand between these two is up as well.
Short and outside off, tapped away off the back foot through the point region for one more.
Short again and there's width on offer, Ollie Pope salps it off the back foot and in front of point for yet another single.
Back of a length outside off, Root hops on the back foot and dabs it down towards the gully region.
This is short and at the body, jabbed away down to deep square leg for a single.
Slower and shorter over leg stump, Joe Root plays a controlled pull shot down to deep backward square leg for one.
FOUR! That has been spanked away! Short and outside off, sitting up nicely for the batter, Ollie Pope backs away and hits it hard well in front of square on the off side for a boundary.
FOUR! Ollie Pope is in overdrive here. This is dug in even shorter by Wagner and over off stump. Pope gives himself a bit of room and slaps it tennis-style over mid on for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Neil Wagner has the last laugh here and seems to have gotten rid of Ollie Pope but the umpires have gone upstairs to check for a fair catch and the soft signal is out. The third umpire checks it a couple of times and is satisfied with the catch. Coming to the delivery, Wagner bangs it in short and over leg stump but it is a bit slower. Pope looks to shuffle a bit and pull it behind square but only manages to get a glove on it. The ball loops up a bit and goes to the right of the keeper. Tom Blundell dives forward to that side and pouches it safely. Wagner is ecstatic and Pope departs on 49.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Neil Wagner

Commentary: Banged in short and over leg stump, Harry Brook pulls it hard but straight to the man at deepish square leg.
Short of a length around leg stump and at 141.5 clicks. Root plays a controlled pull shot down to deep backward square leg for one.
Scott Kuggeleijn bowls a solid bumper now at almost 140 clicks and over off stump. This one flies off the deck and Harry Brook ducks under it.
Pitches it further up now around off and at 141 clicks. Harry Brook is caught on the back foot as he looks to drive and gets an outside edge that lands just in front of the gully fielder.
Scott Kuggeleijn grunts and bangs in another bumper over the stumps, Brook is able to duck under it though.

This is excellent bowling from Scott Kuggeleijn and Harry Brook is lucky not to have edged that. Good length on the fifth stump line and angled in. This one leaves the batter a bit after pitching and Brook has a little nibble at it but gets beaten just past the outside edge.
Back of a length around off, Brook blocks it out.
Shorter and around the hips, Root pulls it down to fine leg for a single.
BYE! A slower short ball this angled well across the right-hander and the ball just keeps on angling away, beating the diving keeper and going toward third man. They pick up a bye.
Another slower bumper over leg stump and this one sticks in the surface a bit. Joe Root goes for the pull but mistimes it a bit uppishly down to fine leg for one more.
Short of a length around leg stump, Harry Brook gets on top of the bounce and pulls it to the right of the man at deep square leg for a couple of runs.

Not far away! Short of a length over middle and leg, Harry Brook nails the pull shot but hits it flat and just over the leaping fielder at square leg for a single. Tom Blundell there reacted quickly and flew to his left but couldn't get a hand on it.
Banged in short at the batter by Neil Wagner, Joe Root shapes to take it on but lets it go through to the keeper.
Good-length delivery around off, Harry Brook pushes this one wide of mid on and takes a single.
On a good length outside off, Joe Root goes back in his crease to defend but gets it from the outer part of the bat towards gully.
Length delivery on off by Scott Kuggeleijn, Joe Root presses forward and defends it to cover for a single.
Back of a length on middle and leg, Harry Brook hangs back and turns this one to square leg for a single.
Keeps it on a good length around off, Joe Root stays back and taps it to cover for a quick single.
Short of a length outside off, Harry Brook dabs this one off the back foot to backward point.
FOUR! Neil Wagner looks to go short again but the ball does not rise, Harry Brook gets into the position early and pulls it towards deep backward square leg for a boundary.
Short and at the batter, Harry Brook swivels in his crease and pulls it straight to backward square leg.
SIX! Short and dispatched by Harry Brook! Goes short again and on middle, Harry Brook backs away and flat bats this one towards the long on fence. Gets enough bat on it and collects a maximum.
Short and around the left shoulder of the batter, Harry Brook does not control his pull shot and hits it uppishly but wide of backward square leg for a single.
Short and down the leg side, Joe Root gets inside the line and helps it to fine leg for a single.

FOUR! Neil Wagner persists with short length and on middle, Harry Brook moves to the leg side and has all the time in the world to get into a position. Flat bats this one through the vacant mid on region for a boundary.
FOUR! Short and angling in on leg, Joe Root gets on top of the bounce and rolls his wrists. Pulls this one towards fine leg for a boundary. The runs keep coming for England.
Short of a length at the batter by Scott Kuggeleijn, Joe Root works this one off the back foot to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Scott Kuggeleijn goes full this time and bowls it outside off, Harry Brook picks the length early and leans into the drive. Gets it to the left of mid off for a boundary.
On a length on middle, Harry Brook gets behind the line and works it to mid-wicket.
Bowls this one short and on off, Harry Brook rides on top of the bounce towards deep mid-wicket and collects a couple of runs.
Full and at the stumps, Harry Brook blocks this one out off the front foot.
Short but down the leg side from over the wicket, Joe Root pulls it along the ground but fails to get it past short fine leg.
Short and aimed at the batter, Joe Root gets into a good position and pulls it to the right of deep square leg for a brace.
Short and angling across on off, Joe Root sways away and lets it go through to the keeper.
Short again on leg, Joe Root gets inside the line and pulls it wide of short fine leg for a single.
Sees the batter shuffle and bowls it on a length at him, Harry Brook moves out of the line and leaves the ball alone.
Short and on middle by Neil Wagner, Harry Brook pulls it hard but straight to square leg.
Starts with a short-of-a-length delivery around off, Joe Root gets on his toes and guides it towards gully.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off by Blair Tickner, Joe Root stands tall and cuts this one through point. Gets it well wide of deep backward point and the fast outfield does the rest.
Goes short again and outside off, Joe Root does not reach out to the delivery and leaves the ball alone.
Keeps it full and around off, Joe Root presses forward and drives it nicely but fails to get it past Michael Bracewell at short cover.

FOUR! Streaky but they all count! Blair Tickner bowls it on a length around off, Joe Root tries to work it on the off side but gets an inside edge that rolls past the keeper for a boundary. 50-run stand comes up between Joe Root and Harry Brook.
Full on off, Joe Root gets on the front foot and drives it to mid off.
Ouch, that must have hurt! Neil Wagner bowls it short and at the batter, Harry Brook gets into his shot early as he tried to pull. Fails to connect and the ball catches him near the ribs.
FOUR! Keeps it short and at the batter, Harry Brook backs away and flat bats this one through the vacant mid off region for a boundary.

FOUR! Short again on middle by Neil Wagner, Harry Brook does not get on top of the bounce and pulls this one high in the air towards deep square leg. Devon Conway stationed there goes for the catch and puts in the dive. The ball falls just short of him and it trickles into the fence.
FOUR! Make that three in a row! Neil Wagner goes short and at the batter, Harry Brook moves to the leg side again and drills this one in tennis style wide of mid off or a boundary.

SIX! Neil Wagner persists with short length and on middle and leg, Harry Brook backs away and flat bats this one towards long on. Gets it from the middle part of the ball and clears the ropes for a maximum.
Short but down the leg side, Harry Brook lets it go through to the keeper.

Blair Tickner bowls this one on a good length but angling on leg, Joe Root gets across to flick this one on the leg side but misses and gets hit on the front pad. New Zealand go up in unison but the umpire shakes his head. After a deliberation, Tim Southee sends it upstairs for a review. The UltraEdge shows no bat but it is missing the stumps on Ball Tracking. The onfield decision stands and New Zealand lose their review.
Shorter in length on middle, Joe Root hangs back and keeps this one out.
Short of a length angling into the batter, Joe Root nudges this one to backward square leg for a single.
Goes into the wicket again and on middle, Harry Brook gets on top of the bounce and defends it on the leg side.
Short of a length on off, Harry Brook steers this one on the bounce towards gully.
Strays on the pads, fuller in length, Harry Brook clips it off his toes and flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Michael Bracewell starts with a flighted delivery, fuller around off, Harry Brook steps out to go through the off side but mishits it to mid-wicket.
Short and on off by Michael Bracewell, Harry Brook goes back in his crease and punches it wide of cover for a couple of runs.
Full and at the stumps, Harry Brook knocks it down to long on for a single.

FIFTY for Joe Root! Bracewell misses his length and bowls a low full toss on off, Joe Root reverse paddles this one towards third man. Kane Williamson runs around and saves a run for his side. This has been a resilient fifty by Joe Root and these are ominous signs for New Zealand.
Floated, full on off, Harry Brook pushes it back to the bowler.

FIFTY for Harry Brook! Short and turning into the batter, Harry Brook goes on the back foot and pushes it down to long on. Takes a single to bring up his fifty. This has been fearless batting by the right-handed batter.
Short of a length on off, Harry Brook dabs this one off the back foot towards gully.
Full and slanting into the batter, Harry Brook drives it along the ground to mid on.
FOUR! Short and just outside off, Harry Brook hangs back and cuts this one late. Gets it past gully and the ball races away to the fence.

OUT! CAUGHT! Blair Tickner finally gets his man and removes Harry Brook! Bowls this one on a good length in the channel outside off, Harry Brook is neither forward nor back and pokes at the delivery. The ball catches the outside edge and it travels first slip. Daryl Mitchell reacts quickly and gets low to his left. Takes a sharp catch to bring an end to a fine knock by Harry Brook. This is a much-needed breakthrough for New Zealand.
Howout: c Daryl Mitchell b Blair Tickner

Commentary: Blair Tickner welcomes Ben Foakes with a bumper! Bowls it short and at the batter, Ben Foakes ducks under it and lets it go through to the keeper.
On a length around off, Ben Foakes solidly defends on the off side.
Slower and short, turning in on off, Joe Root smothers the ball down the wicket.
Short and turning into the batter, Joe Root goes back and turns it towards backward square leg for a single.
Flighted delivery, full outside off, Ben Foakes takes a big stride forward to defend but gets rapped on the front pad.
Short and quicker at the stumps, Ben Foakes works this one off his hips to deep backward square leg. Opens his account with a single.
Floated, full on off, Joe Root gets down and sweeps it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Full around off by Michael Bracewell, Ben Foakes gets forward and keeps it out.
On a good length outside off, Joe Root takes a stride forward to defend but gets it from the outer part of the bat towards gully.
Fraction short and outside off, Joe Root hangs back and dabs it to deep backward point for a single.
Goes full this time and at the stumps, Ben Foakes gets behind the line and pushes it back to the bowler.
Short and aimed at the batter, Ben Foakes ducks under the delivery and leaves the ball alone.
Full and on middle and leg, Ben Foakes clips this one wide of Kane Williamson at mid on and takes a single.
Back of a length and angling in on middle, Joe Root stays on the back foot and defends it on the off side.
Flighted, full outside off, Ben Foakes steps out and flicks this one uppishly towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Full on off, Ben Foakes gets forward and smothers the ball on the off side.
Tossed up, full outside off, Ben Foakes gets across and pushes it to mid-wicket.
Short and at the stumps, Ben Foakes stays back and works it to mid-wicket.
Full and quicker on middle, Ben Foakes gets behind the line and turns this one to mid-wicket.
Floated, full outside off by Michael Bracewell, Ben Foakes drives it along the ground to mid on.
Short and outside off, Joe Root swivels in his crease and drags this one to deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length in the channel outside off, Ben Foakes hangs back and dabs it to point.
Full and angling down the leg side, Ben Foakes gets inside the line and works it to fine leg for a run.
Full and on middle and leg, Joe Root gets into the positon early and clips it off his toes. Gets it wide of deep square leg which allows him to complete the second run with ease.
Fuller in length outside off, Joe Root presses forward and guides it towards backward point for a single.
Banged in short at the batter by Blair Tickner, Ben Foakes ducks under it and lets it go through to the keeper.

OUT! CAUGHT! Joe Root is gone in the final over before tea! Michael Bracewell bowls this one full and outside off, Joe Root pulls out the reverse sweep but gets a glove on it. The ball takes the glove of Tom Blundell behind the wicket and lobs to Daryl Mitchell at first slip who does the rest. Joe Root is distraught as he was looking so good out in the middle. That will be Tea on Day 3!
Howout: c Daryl Mitchell b Michael Bracewell

Commentary: Full and at the stumps, Ben Stokes keeps it out.
Full again around off, Ben Stokes gets forward and defends it on the off side.
Full and turning away outside off, Ben Stokes leaves the ball alone.
Short and outside off, Ben Stokes goes back and punches it to cover.
Full and around off, Ben Stokes gets forward and smothers the ball on the off side.
Goes full and at the stumps, Ben Foakes drives this one to mid on.
Banged in short and outside off by Scott Kuggeleijn, Ben Foakes sways away and leaves the ball alone.
Back of a length on middle, Ben Foakes hangs back and whips this one to mid-wicket.
On a good length around off, Ben Foakes gets behind the line and defends it down the wicket.
Slower and full on leg, Ben Foakes waits for it and clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Length delivery angling across outside off, Ben Stokes dabs this one from the crease to backward point.
Tossed up, full at the pads, Ben Foakes works this one to mid-wicket.
Flighted, full and turning in on leg, Ben Foakes steps out and helps this one towards fine leg for three runs.
Full and drifting in on middle, Ben Stokes can only push this one to extra cover.
Short and flatter on middle, Ben Stokes goes back in his crease and defends it on the off side.
Goes full and on middle, Ben Stokes presses forward and blocks this one out.
Floated, full on middle, Ben Stokes takes a stride forward and defends this one back to the bowler.
Full and around off by Scott Kuggeleijn, Ben Foakes gets behind the line and defends it down the wicket.
Banged in short and outside off, Ben Foakes gets on top of the bounce and pulls it along the ground to deep square leg for a single.
On a length angling across on off, Ben Stokes hangs back and defends it on the off side.
Fuller and slanting away outside off, Ben Stokes shoulders arms and lets it go.

FOUR! Nicely played! Short and aimed at the batter by Scott Kuggeleijn, Ben Stokes swivels in his crease and plays a controlled pull shot. Gets it towards deep backward square leg and opens his account with a boundary.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Ben Stokes! Scott Kuggeleijn bowls this one on a length on middle, Ben Stokes shimmies down the track and opens the bat face to guide it past backward point for yet another boundary.
Full and quicker outside off, Ben Foakes gets forward and smothers the ball on the off side.
Full and darted on off, Ben Foakes takes a stride forward and defends it to cover.
Short and flatter outside off, the ball keeps a bit low but Ben Foakes manages to keep this one out.
Short and outside off, Ben Foakes pushes this one off the back foot to point for a single.
Full and drifting in on middle, Ben Stokes uses his feet and pushes it to mid off for a quick single.
Short and turning in on middle, Ben Foakes gets across and works it to short leg.
Back of a length on off from 'round the wicket, Ben Stokes hangs back and taps it towards cover for a single.
Scott Kuggeleijn misses his line and length and bowls a low full toss down the leg side, Ben Foakes goes for the flick but misses.
Good bumper! Scott Kuggeleijn bangs this one short and at the batter, Ben Foakes gets inside the line and ducks under the delivery.
Goes full and straight at the stumps, Ben Foakes gets behind the line and defends it back to the bowler.

FOUR! A wayward delivery by Scott Kuggeleijn, low full toss at the pads, Ben Foakes tries to help this one fine on the leg side. Tries to work it fine but it comes off his back leg and it races away to the ropes for a boundary. However, the umpire thinks it has come off Ben Foakes' bat.
WIDE! Banged in short by Scott Kuggeleijn, Ben Foakes ducks under it and lets it go. The ball sails over the batter's head and it is signalled as wide.
Goes full and on middle, Ben Foakes pushes it back to the bowler for a dot.
Short and quicker around off, Ben Stokes goes back in his crease to cut but misses.
Short and at the stumps, Ben Stokes stays on the back foot and knocks it down to long on for a single.
Fuller on middle, Ben Foakes defends it down the wicket.
Short and angling in at the pads, Ben Foakes flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted, full and turning away outside off, Ben Stokes gets down to slog sweep but does not connect.
Full and outside off, Ben Stokes accounts for the away turn and leaves the ball alone.
Bowled short from around the wicket and around leg stump, Foakes gets inside the line and pulls it down to fine leg for one.
A bumper now around leg stump and angling further down, Ben Stokes just walks across the off stump and leaves it alone.

SIX! All the way! Short again and angling down leg, but just not short enough. Ben Stokes pulls it over the fine leg fence and there's a huge roar from the crowd as Stokes becomes the player to hit the most number os maximums in Test matches. Phenomenal achievement! And guess who he overtakes? Former Kiwi batter and now England's coach Brendon McCullum.

SIX! Oh, no! Neil Wagner has made a mess of that one. Banged in short and over leg stump, Ben Stokes goes for the pull but hits it straight around the face of Wagner who is stationed right on the fine leg fence. Wagner grabs it with both hands but fails to keep his balance and falls over the ropes, resulting in another maximum.
Short and around off, dabbed down to the right of backward point.
A good bouncer now bowled from over the stumps and angled across the batter. Stokes looks to upper cut it but misses.
Tossed up on a length and turning into middle, Ben Foakes pushes it uppishly but well in front of short leg.
Bowls it shorter and turns it in from outside off, Foakes defends it down the pitch.
FOUR! Good shot! Tossed up outside off and turning in, Ben Foakes uses his feet and whips it over the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Flighted delivery around off, Foakes advances and pushes it to the left of mid on for a quick single.
Floated up around off, Ben Stokes defends it off the front foot.

A huge appeal for lbw but it is turned down! This is bowled flatter from around the stumps and angling it in from outside off. Stokes gets a big stride across as he looks to sweep it fine but seems to have missed it and gets hit on the pads. No review was taken by New Zealand and the replays show that there might have been an inside edge.
Banged in short at the batter from 'round the wicket, Ben Foakes rolls his wrists and pulls this one but fails to get it past Kane Williamson at backward square leg.
FOUR! Short of a length on leg, Ben Foakes gets on top of the bounce and pulls it well wide of fine leg and the fast outfield does the rest. The lead goes past 300 now.
Short and again down the leg side, Ben Foakes rises and pulls it down to fine leg for a single.
WIDE! Persists with the short stuff but this time goes too short and the ball sails over the head of Ben Stokes.

Good running! Scott Kuggeleijn bowls a full toss outside off, Ben Stokes shimmies down the track and reaches out to the delivery. Drives it wide of deep point which allows him to come back for the second with relative ease.
Shortens his length and bowls it on off, Ben Stokes hangs back and dabs it past backward point for a single. 50-run stand comes up Ben Stokes and Ben Foakes.
Back of a length and angling on leg, Ben Foakes stays on the back foot and works it straight to short fine leg.
FOUR! Michael Bracewell bowls this one a bit too full on off, Ben Stokes steps out and gets to the ball in flash. Uses his bottom hand and drills it past mid off for a boundary.
Tossed up, slower and full around off, Ben Stokes presses forward and smothers the ball on the off side.
Short and on off, Ben Stokes punches it wide of long off for a single.
Short and at the stumps, Ben Foakes works it straight to short leg where Tom Latham makes a good stop.
Short and flatter on leg, Ben Foakes works it off the back foot to backward square leg for a single.

OUT! STUMPED! A huge wicket for New Zealand! Michael Bracewell floats this one nicely, fuller and outside off, Ben Stokes gets tempted by the flight and advances down the track to go down the ground. Swings his bat but gets beaten in the flight and the ball spins past his outside edge. Tom Blundell behind the wicket collects it cleanly and does the rest. Michael Bracewell is delighted and so he should be.
Howout: st Tom Blundell b Michael Bracewell

Commentary: Full but down the leg side from 'round the wicket, Ben Foakes goes for the flick but misses.

FOUR! Nicely played! Scott Kuggeleijn bowls this one slower and full on middle and leg, Ben Foakes waits for it and drives this one along the ground. Gets it wide of mid on and the ball races away for a boundary.
Goes short this time at the batter, Ben Foakes swivels and pulls it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Back of a length around off by Scott Kuggeleijn, Ollie Robinson hangs back and pushes it to cover for a single.
Short and aimed at the batter, Ben Foakes gets across to pull it on the leg side but gets rapped on the gloves. Takes his glove off and calls for the physio.

FOUR! Easy pickings! Scott Kuggeleijn bowls this one short of a length but down the leg side, Ben Foakes gets inside the line and uses the angle to his advantage. Helps it to the right of the fine leg fielder and picks up a boundary.
FOUR! Michael Bracewell misses his length and fires in a low full toss at the stumps, Ollie Robinson pulls out the reverse sweep and gets it through backward point for a boundary.
Flighted, full around off, Ollie Robinson goes for the reverse sweep again and gets this one past first slip. Three runs taken.
Tossed up, full on off, Ben Foakes steps out and flicks it towards mid on for a single.
Slower and full, turning into the batter, Ollie Robinson gets behind the line and keeps this one out.
Short and quicker at the stumps, Ollie Robinson goes back and pushes it to mid on.

Michael Bracewell bowls this one full and on middle, Ollie Robinson presses forward to defend but gets beaten on the inside edge and gets rapped on the front pad. A loud shout but it is turned down by the umpire. New Zealand go upstairs for a review but the UltraEdge shows a spike as the ball is next to the bat. The on-field decision stands and New Zealand lose their review.
Tim Southee comes back into the attack and starts with a pitched-up delivery on off stump, Ben Foakes pushes it straight back to mid off.
Fullish length in that channel around off and this is kept out off the front foot.
Pitched up just a bit wider of the off stump, Foakes gets forward and punches it out to cover.
Fuller in length and around off, Foakes pushes it toward wide mid off and scampers across for the single.
A length ball on leg stump, Ollie Robinson tucks it away in front of square on the leg side for a single.
Goes full on off and tries to swing it away, Foakes defends it back to the bowler.
Nicely tossed up on a shorter length and outside off, turning in, Ollie Robinson keeps it down in front of short leg.
FOUR! NIcely done! Shorter and turning in from around off, Ollie Robinson shuffles across and whips it behind square leg for a boundary.
A bit flatter and around middle, kept out by Robinson.
Nagging length, pushed through a bit quicker and around off, Ollie Robinson gets on the back foot to defend.
A tad short and wide, Robinson backs away and misses out on the cut as he gets an inside edge that goes past the off stump.
